{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/unlocking-business-value-from-machine-learning-model-interpretability-c08100b788c8", "time": 1682993843.363032, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/unlocking-business-value-from-machine-learning-model-interpretability-c08100b788c8/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Unlocking Business Value from Machine Learning: Model Interpretability | by Shayaan Jagtap | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Unlocking Business Value from Machine Learning: Model Interpretability", "description": "It\u2019s the AI revolution. If your company isn\u2019t mining data, shoving it into a neural network, and marketing its advanced AI capabilities, you\u2019re already behind the curve\u2026 right? Not quite. For the\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://medium.com/greyatom/performance-metrics-for-classification-problems-in-machine-learning-part-i-b085d432082b", "anchor_text": "performance metrics", "paragraph_index": 11}], "all_paragraphs": ["It\u2019s the AI revolution. If your company isn\u2019t mining data, shoving it into a neural network, and marketing its advanced AI capabilities, you\u2019re already behind the curve\u2026 right? Not quite.", "For the same reason that star players make bad coaches, models that make complicated decisions at high levels of abstraction come at a price, they can\u2019t easily explain their reasoning. This is a direct (and sometimes expensive) tradeoff.", "There is a similar paradigm for machine learning. The more powerful the model, the harder it is to interpret its inner workings. Sure, you may get a more accurate answer from a neural network, but how it arrived at that answer may be a total mystery. This can be a problem when trying to figure out what went wrong or how to improve it.", "Modern marketing has solidified \u201cdeep learning neural network\u201d as a contender for sexiest four word phrase in tech. But, data scientists know that fancier doesn\u2019t always mean better.", "What if I told you that real business value is not necessarily tied to the \u201csophistication\u201d of your model?", "Interpretability is used to seek an understanding of the complicated nature between inputs and outputs.", "Let\u2019s take a simple example: predicting yearly household spend. Using a neural network, I may get the perfect predictor of every dollar that leaves every hand in the country. That\u2019s great, but what if I want to know how inputs contribute to that spend?", "How much more expensive is the average dog? The average kid? Increased income? These factors definitely contribute to spending, but how much each one adds may be a total mystery at higher levels of decision making.", "Due to the complex, abstract nature of how a NN transforms inputs into outputs, attempting to understand it is hopeless.", "Conversely, a simple linear regression may hold those answers. While not as accurate, it will certainly be easier to understand.", "Whether you choose a linear regression, neural network, or anything in between, may largely depend on your goal \u2014 to use or understand the machine. In other words, do you need a good player or a good coach?", "It all comes down to what\u2019s more valuable for your business: maximizing performance metrics or understanding input-output relationships?", "For example, denying a loan application on the basis of \u201cI don\u2019t know, the machine just said so\u201d is not good enough. Life altering decisions should be communicated clearly, and decisions should be fair.", "This is the basis for unlocking value from interpretability \u2014 a customer that is informed is a customer that trusts you.", "There is one more thing worth mentioning: The importance of clear inputs.", "Selecting the right inputs is crucial to building an interpretable model. Intuitive input-output interpretations are only possible if your inputs make sense to begin with. For example, consider the following two features:", "Clearly feature 1 will make more sense to interpret: \u201cFor each additional child, a household will spend $10,000 more a year on average\u201d versus \u201cFor every increase in square root of income, average spending goes up by $.25 a year\u201d.", "Even though the second one may make for a more accurate model, intuitively it makes no sense. It is crucial that inputs are intuitive \u2014 our customers, and our decisions, may rely on it.", "Today\u2019s explosion of deep learning is awesome, but we should not forget the fundamentals.", "There is a reason most business school statistics courses focus on linear and logistic regression. Clear understanding leads to good decision making, effective communication, and customers that trust you.", "In the end, I guess this was a long-winded way of saying \u201chey, sometimes the customer needs to know what\u2019s going on, too.\u201d", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "data scientist \u2014 software developer \u2014 thinker of thoughts"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2Fc08100b788c8&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Funlocking-business-value-from-machine-learning-model-interpretability-c08100b788c8&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Funlocking-business-value-from-machine-learning-model-interpretability-c08100b788c8&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "